ate may pursue recovery of paid benefits through repayment rights, either from settlements or judgments recovered by the insured. This right is exercised when a responsible party is identified, and Allstate may seek reimbursement from jointly responsible parties. Additionally, Allstate covers defense costs and loss of wages for insured persons attending hearings, reinforcing its role as a legal and financial protector. These mechanisms ensure that financial exposure is mitigated and that the insured is not left bearing full liability [Data: Entities (270, 272, 279, 280, 281, 282, 283, 289, 304, 331, 332, 335, 391, 392, 393, 394, 485, 486, 492, 494, 495, 496, 497, 500, 503, 686, 687, 688, 689, 690, 698, 699, 700, 701, +more); Relationships (270, 272, 469, 492, 494, 495, 496, 497, 500, 503, 686, 687, 688, 689, 690, 698, 699, 700, 701, +more)].\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"summary\": \"Coverage sharing and exhaustion rules to prevent double recovery\",\n            \"explanation\": \"Allstate enforces strict rules to prevent overlapping or excessive payouts. Coverage sharing ensures that Allstate’s liability is determined in proportion to its policy limits compared to other applicable policies. Additionally, the policy mandates coverage exhaustion—Allstate will only pay after all other collectible insurance has been fully used. This prevents double recovery and ensures fairness in multi-policy scenarios. The principle of 'broadest coverage' further limits recovery to a single, most comprehensive policy, reinforcing the integrity of the claims process. These rules are critical in managing risk and ensuring equitable outcomes across complex liability situations [Data: Entities (386, 391, 392, 393, 394, 485, 486, 492, 494, 495, 496, 497, 500, 503, 686, 687, 688, 689, 690, 698, 699, 700, 701, +more); Relationships (386, 391, 392, 393, 394, 485, 486, 492, 494, 495, 496, 497, 500, 503, 686, 687, 688, 689, 690, 698, 699, 700, 701, +more)].\"\n        }\n    ],\n   